   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <hazardstatement type="danger" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">Heavy movable system</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Always check that all cables, connection and installations
are removed before transporting the system.</howtoavoid>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Never perform any installation, maintenance or operate
the system if it is only locked by the wheel brakes. Move the system
to the brackets and lock it into place, see <xref href="1230097_Lock_the_System_In_the_Brackets_TSK_DD00730782.dita"
                        scope="local"
                        type="task"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <hazardstatement type="warning" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">Incorrect transportation</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Only move the system on wheels after all the transport
units have been assembled.</howtoavoid>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Only move the system when all eight wheels are mounted.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Use the mounted wheels to transport
the complete system, consisting of several transport units.</p>
         <note class="- topic/note ">The wheels have breaks that can temporally prevent the system from
moving. The breaks should not be used to keep the system in place
for a long period of time, it is recommended to move the system to
the location of the brackets and lock it in place.</note>
